\name{benchfigR-package}
\alias{benchfigR-package}
\alias{benchfigR}
\title{NC-Style Benchmark and Biological Case Figure Toolkit}
\description{
Local R toolkit for NC-style benchmark and biological case figures from source-data tables.
}
\details{
The package is source-data-first and supports metric heatmaps, rank summaries,
runtime/memory plots, robustness curves, representative case embeddings, and
composite benchmark plus biological case figures. It depends on \pkg{ncfigR}
for shared theme, layout, and export.
}
